	<h1>Resources</h1>
	<p>
		The Movies and Dramatics Club offers a range of resources to support our
		members in their creative endeavors. Whether you're looking for scripts,
		production guides, or inspiration, we've got you covered. Here are some of
		the key resources we provide:
	</p>
	<h2>Script Library</h2>
	<p>
		Our extensive script library includes a wide variety of plays, monologues,
		and scenes. Whether you're looking for classic works or contemporary pieces,
		you'll find something to suit your needs.
	</p>
	<h2>Production Guides</h2>
	<p>
		We provide detailed guides on all aspects of production, from directing and
		stage management to costume design and lighting. These guides are invaluable
		for anyone looking to take on a leadership role in a production.
	</p>
	<h2>Workshops and Tutorials</h2>
	<p>
		In addition to our regular workshops, we offer a range of online tutorials
		and resources covering various aspects of acting and production. These
		resources are perfect for members who want to continue learning and
		developing their skills outside of regular club activities.
	</p>
	<h2>Networking Opportunities</h2>
	<p>
		Our club provides numerous opportunities for members to connect with
		industry professionals and like-minded peers. These connections can be
		invaluable for anyone looking to pursue a career in the performing arts.
	</p>
	<h2>Mentorship Program</h2>
	<p>
		Our mentorship program pairs experienced members with newer members to
		provide guidance and support. This program is a great way for newer members
		to learn the ropes and for experienced members to give back to the club.
	</p>
